                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-08-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Jackson, chargé, reports the willingness of Japan and Russia to put their
                    forces under the chief command of Field Marshal Count Waldersee in Chihli. Says
                    the German Government would like to know views entertained by United States
                    Government in regard to chief in command, and in what way it would be inclined
                    to join the American forces in Chihli to the army operating under
                    Waldersee.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
